.TH GIT-FOLDER 1 "2026-04-09" "git-folder" "Git Manual"
.SH NAME
git-folder \- manage groups of git branches as folders
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git folder
.I <command>
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-folder
is a git subcommand for managing groups of branches as folders. It focuses on managing sequences of numbers, like
.IR async/1 ,
.IR async/2 ,
etc.

The tool helps preserve work during iterative development by maintaining numbered branch sequences, so you can experiment freely while keeping prior work accessible.

When iterating on an idea, it's sometimes useful to keep prior branches around. In case of a failed experiment, this can spare you from lost time poring over a crowded reflog. Or sometimes, it's handy to preserve a series of commits you made during development; but you also need to squash and rebase that work to move forward.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B delete <folder>
Delete all branches in folder
.TP
.B delete-upto <folder> <n>
Delete numbered branches below n
.TP
.B increment [folder]
Create and checkout next numbered branch
.TP
.B last-number [folder]
Print highest numbered branch
.TP
.B list [folder]
List branches in folder
.TP
.B rename <existing> <new>
Rename folder prefix
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
.B \-\-nocheckout
(increment only) Create branch without checking out
.SH NOTES
When
.I [folder]
is omitted, defaults to folder of current branch, if applicable.

The
.B delete
and
.B delete-upto
commands have confirmation prompts (skipped with \-\-force).

The
.B increment
command errors if any other than the highest branch is used for the default. If folder is specified (rather than using default), creates a new branch from the highest numbered branch.
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a series of branches while working on an async conversion:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ git checkout -b async/1
$ # ... make 7 commits ...
$ git folder increment
creating async/2
$ # ... squash and rebase ...
$ git folder list async
async/1
async/2
.RE
.fi
.PP
Delete old experimental branches:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ git folder delete-upto async 3
.RE
.fi
.SH AUTHOR
Clay Bridges
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR git-branch (1)
